intro: Dillwynia capitata var. uliginosa, commonly known as the swamp dillwynia, is a flowering plant native to eastern Australia. It belongs to the Fabaceae family, characterized by its compound leaves and pod-like fruits. The plant typically grows in wet or swampy areas, thriving in poorly drained soils. It produces small, fragrant white or pale yellow flowers arranged in dense spikes. Its botanical features make it an important component of wetland ecosystems.
